  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly:  "H. Creticus/Criticus Greek periegete, 3rd cent. BC, Greek 
    periegete of the 3rd cent. BC, author of the treatise Per&#xEC; t&#xF4;n en t&#xEA;i Hell&#xE1;di p&#xF3;le&#x14D;n (&#x2018;On the Towns of Greece&#x2019;), 
    which describes a journey through central and northern Greece
    ....The work has usually been attributed since its first edition by H. Stephanus in 1589 to
    Dicaearchus, but a note in the paradoxographer Apollonius [2. 120-142 &#xA7; 19] (2nd cent. BC?) attests author and title.."
    Brodersen, Kai (Mannheim).  "Heraclides." Brill&#x2019;s New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and , 
    Helmuth Schneider. Brill Online, 2013. Reference. Tufts University Library.</mads:note>
